name settled there 200 years later in Tipperary and surrounding counties.","North German and Dutch: patronymic from a short form of any of various ancient Germanic compound personal names beginning with <i>hard</i> ‘hardy, brave, strong’, or a habitational name from a farm named Harding, of the same etymology.","History: Warren Gamaliel Harding (1865–1923), the 29th president of the US, was born on a farm in OH, of English and Scottish stock on his father's side. Early American bearers of this very common name include Joseph Harding who died at Plymouth in 1633. His great-great grandson Seth was a naval officer during the American Revolution."],"variants":[{"name":"Hardin","meanings":["English: variant of   Harding  .","Altered form of French   Hardouin  .","French: from a pet form of any of several ancient Germanic personal names composed of the element <i>hard</i> ‘hard, strong’. This surname is rare in France."]},{"name":"Arduino","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Francisco, Jose, Luis, Marina, Alberto, Alfonso, Alturo, Angel, Arturo, Azucena, Basilio, Carlos.  Italian Antonio, Gabino.","Italian and Hispanic: from the personal name <i>Arduino</i>, which is of ancient Germanic origin, akin to   Harding   2."]}]},{"name":"Ralph","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Ralf","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":25,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title